I am a big fan of your show, YouTube Channel and Instagram.

One day last week I was scrolling through my Instagram and saw the article from people magazine. As soon as I saw this article I sent it straight to my twin sister Nicole. We are so both excited for you and your family. Funny thing is me and my sister are also pregnant and due the same week in July. What a miracle. We really enjoy following and listening to your channel. It is so crazy how similar our stories are from finding out during Thanksgiving to having the same symptoms together. Thank you for sharing your experiences we hope to hear and learn more about your pregnancy experience.

snippet.textDisplay: My 1st pregnancy went SO easy until the 3rd trimester. Still, it was Nothing. This pregnancy... It's a completely different story. I was dealing with terrible morning sickness, all day, for the 1st trimester. Now that I'm in my second, I still get hit, really bad on some days, or nights. And it comes out of nowhere. If it's not that, then it's bad indigestion. I was laying in bed getting ready to fall asleep a week or so ago and had to run to the bathroom. My husband was laughing and poking fun. Which helps me because, I don't take myself too serious that way. I understand that this won't work for everyone. But if something like that does happen, and you think it might work for you. Try to find some kind of humor in it.
